  "description": "Karl Harry, born on December 1, 1895 in Borås, was a Swedish Vice Consul. He was married to Martha Johansson-Rutstedt. They had three children: Bengt (born in 1929), Åke (born in 1931), and Göran (born in 1936). Karl established himself after an internship at the textile company Bröderna Wennerlund in Borås in 1917. In 1937, he became the Polish Vice Consul. Karl was actively involved in various organizations and committees, including the Älvsborg County Solsticka, Borås Summer Colony, Vetritas Church Building Committee, and Borås Scout Troop. He also held positions such as Secretary of the Children's Day, board member of the Swedish Red Cross Älvsib District, and board member of A-B Borås Tennishall. Karl participated in business study trips to several European countries, the USA, Mexico, West Indies, North Africa, Egypt, Palestine, Syria, among others. He was a member of Frimurarorden, Odd Fellows, Knight Templar Order, and the 95-year-old men's club. Karl Harry passed away on an unknown date."
